/-
This module proves the "Cubic Collapse" theorem for K=4 symmetric update matrices.
It establishes that for symmetric matrices Σᵢ and update operators Aᵢ = I - γᵢΣᵢ,
the trace of the product A₄A₃A₂A₁ is equal to the trace of the reversed product A₁A₂A₃A₄.
This implies that cubic terms in the expansion which change sign under reversal must vanish.
The result is generalized to K=3 and K=5 as well, demonstrating a general palindrome symmetry for traces of products of symmetric matrices.
-/

